Sentencas: A perovskite-type BaCe0.5Fe0.3Bi0.2O3-(delta) (BCFB) was employed as a novel cathode material for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: A novel BaCe0.5Fe0.3Bi0.2O3-δ perovskite-type cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The single cells with the structure of NiO-BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-delta (BZCY7) anode substrate vertical bar NiO-BZCY7 anode functional layer vertical bar BZCY7 electrolyte membrane I BCFB cathode layer were fabricated by a dry-pressing method and investigated from 550 to 700 degrees C with humidified hydrogen (similar to 3% H2O) as the fuel and the static air as the oxidant.
Titulo: A novel BaCe0.5Fe0.3Bi0.2O3-δ perovskite-type cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The low interfacial polarization resistance of 0.098 Omega cm(2) and the maximum power density of 736 mW cm(-2) are achieved at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: A novel BaCe0.5Fe0.3Bi0.2O3-δ perovskite-type cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The excellent electrochemical performance indicates that BCFB may be a promising cathode material for proton-conducting SOFCs.
Titulo: A novel BaCe0.5Fe0.3Bi0.2O3-δ perovskite-type cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells
